# Speedrun give-up thresholds

The Speedrun give-up thresholds are intentionally set low for the current demo
deck (**3 per topic**):

- `MIN_ANSWERED = 3` in `speedrun/performance_score.py` (question/performance give-up)
- `MIN_REVIEWED = 3` in `speedrun/memory_score.py` (memory give-up; also gates
  when the loop stops serving flashcards and lets a topic into question blocks)

## Reminder

When the user adds more problems to `speedrun/questions.json` (including
AI-generated questions), or grows the flashcard deck, **proactively remind them
to raise these thresholds** (toward 10-15, or ~200 reviewed cards for a full
production deck). Higher thresholds make the memory/performance scores and the
adaptive loop's gap detection more statistically meaningful.
